sources.description:
Stars: Tim McCoy, Pauline Haddon, Lou Fulton, Forrest Taylor
Director: Sam Newfield

Dive into the thrilling world of classic Westerns with Arizona Gang Busters (1940), starring legendary cowboy hero Tim McCoy, the captivating Pauline Haddon, and dynamic performances by Lou Fulton and Forrest Taylor. Directed by Peter Stewart, this action-packed Western delivers a high-stakes tale of espionage, false accusations, and borderland intrigue.

When a group of spies, led by the sinister Schmidt, starts amassing an arsenal along the U.S.-Mexico border, Trigger Tim (McCoy) and his ally Gringo are tasked with stopping them. But the mission takes a dangerous turn when they‚Äôre framed for murder! Arrested and on the run, these unlikely heroes must outwit the law, uncover the truth, and take down the enemy.

From Sigmund Neufeld Productions and distributed by Producers Releasing Corp., this gem captures the essence of 1940s Westerns, blending gun-slinging action, compelling characters, and a gripping plot.

Perfect for fans of Tim McCoy classics, Western outlaws, and PizzaFLIX, Arizona Gang Busters is a must-watch for anyone who loves timeless cowboy adventures and tales of justice in the Old West. Don‚Äôt miss this thrilling ride!
